Pakistan's Prime Minister Khan calls for UN intervention in Kashmir
With an emotional appeal, Pakistan's Prime Minister Imran Khan once again called on the United Nations to intervene in the Kashmir conflict in his first appearance before the UN General Assembly.
Otherwise, a new war between the nuclear powers Pakistan and India is likely, Khan said on Friday at the UN General Debate in New York. "If things go badly, you hope for the best, but be prepared for the worst." The United Nations has a responsibility for Kashmir. "You should have prevented this."
