The demonstrators in Cairo are demanding the overthrow of Egyptian President al-Sisi.
The government is reacting with a heavy hand to the current protests in Egypt. It shoots live ammunition at the population, more than 2,000 detainees join the 60,000 political prisoners already held there in prisons. Protesting in Egypt has never been without danger. But since General Abdel Fattah el-Sisi came to power in 2013, the state apparatus has been doing everything it can to avoid a scenario like the Arab Spring.
