Strike against cybercriminals - investigators dig up servers
In the fight against crimes on the Internet, German investigators have for the first time excavated a large server provider for illegal business in the Darknet.
A total of 13 perpetrators are suspected of having hosted numerous websites as operators of a data center in a former NATO bunker in Traben-Trarbach on the Moselle, through which internationally active criminals operated their machinations.
This was announced by the General Prosecutor's Office in Koblenz. Seven suspects were arrested on Thursday evening in a major operation. The Darknet is a shielded part of the Internet.
Customers of the suspects are said to have been, among other things, the operators of the world's second largest darknet marketplace for drugs, "Wall Street Market" – investigators had smashed in the spring. The attack on 1.25 million Telekom routers at the end of November 2016 was also controlled via a server in the cyberbunker, according to the Attorney General's Office.
